            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Alien Origins",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "text": "Monster scholars disagree on the origins of the deculi. The creature\u2019s familiar batlike anatomy and predilection for caverns suggests an evolution in the Darklands, but its ability to dip in and out of its own personal extradimensional space is far from typical for purely subterranean creatures. Further complicating all of this is the deculi\u2019s infrared vision, which anatomists agree is completely unheard of in mammalian species on Golarion. The most credible theories suggest that the deculi is not from Golarion at all, but arrived here long ago from some part of the Material Plane beyond the reckoning of most mortals.",
